{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
According to DoD, \u8220\'3f[s]ince the Vietnam War ... Congress has confronted \u8216\'3fdisaffection\u8217\'3f with regard to the military among some students and faculty at institutions of higher learning that impairs the ability of the military to recruit.\u8221\'3f Mem. Opp. Summ. J. at 3. In response, the Congress has passed numerous pieces of legislation over the years \u8220\'3f[t]o encourage educational institutions to open their campuses to military recruiters\u8221\'3f by prohibiting the \u8220\'3fdistribution of certain federal funds to institutions of higher learning that barred military recruiters from their campuses.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
