}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=10USCAS983&originatingDoc=I1612b8c476ee11d9ac1ffa9f33b6c3b0&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
10 U.S.C. \u167\'3f 983
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Among other things, the Solomon Amendment denies certain categories of federal funding to institutions of higher education that prevent military recruitment on campus. 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=10USCAS983&originatingDoc=I1612b8c476ee11d9ac1ffa9f33b6c3b0&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.UserEnteredCitation)#co_pp_a83b000018c76" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf20 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
10 U.S.C. \u167\'3f 983(b)
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. On October 28, 2004, Congress amended the Solomon Amendment. 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See
