{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The claims brought by the Faculty and those brought by Professor Rubenfeld are not coextensive. Both the Faculty and Professor Rubenfeld assert that YLS is in compliance with the Solomon Amendment, as amended. They argue that because the FIP and SIP occur off-campus, YLS\rquote  refusal to permit military recruiters access to CDO-run programs does not constitute denying military recruiters \u8220\'3faccess to campus\u8221\'3f or \u8220\'3faccess to students on campus.\u8221\'3f Furthermore, the Faculty and Rubenfeld argue that, because the military is subject to the same YLS policy requiring employers to subscribe to the NDP in order to participate in the CDO recruiting program as every other employer, YLS is offering access to military recruiters that is \u8220\'3fequal in quality and scope\u8221\'3f to that granted to non-military recruiters because the military is welcome to sign the NDP and access the CDO.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
