The Second Circuit has considered a variety of factors in evaluating whether a case is ripe for adjudication: (1) whether the issue to be reviewed is more legal or factual in nature; (2) whether the agency action is likely to have an immediate and substantial impact upon the complaining party; (3) whether judicial review would delay or impede effective enforcement or the relevant administrative scheme; (4) whether the agency\rquote s actions are final, and (5) whether an adequate factual record has been established. 
}
